Icon request checklist

  • This is a single icon or matched pair (Ex: lock / unlock)
  • The title starts with "Icon request: " and is followed by the requested icon name (Ex: Icon request: magical-unicorn)
  • I have searched for existing issues and to the best of my knowledge this is not a duplicate
  • I have included at least one example image if it could be helpful (optional)
  • The request is for a concrete object (it's harder to make an icon to represent happiness, it's easier to make a smiley face. ☺)

digimbyte commented Jan 28, 2021 •
edited

Hi @KDITGEEK thanks for the suggestion, but please use a plain C.

As per our documentation for Brand logos:

This work includes material that may be protected as a trademark in some jurisdictions. If you want to use it, you have to ensure that you have the legal right to do so and that you do not infringe any trademark rights. The use of these trademarks does not indicate endorsement of the trademark holder by Font Awesome, nor vice versa. See the trademark owner for rules about the appropriate use of their trademarks.

Ref: https://fontawesome.com/icons/cuttlefish?style=brands

Reopening here

There was no copyright infringement,
I would like to draw onto the limitations of copyright
https://www.owe.com/resources/legalities/legalities-15-is-a-shape-copyrightable-how-to-get-appropriate-rights-when-you-commission-graphic-design/

Also, the similarities between the original and the 'cuttlefish' are only present in that at least 50% of the body while the other half has diverged in different ways.
The cuttlefish is split with a secondary elliptical shape while the original post used a linear cut.
the cuttlefish also incorporates a minor flair, elongating the right-hand portion away from a symmetrical circle.

Under common copyright, artworks that derive from other or similar works must be at least 30% to avoid infringement, I find them to be at least 50% different, and the other half to be similar but 1, does not match the thickness, and 2, is considered a primitive shape and is not copyright protected regardless.
for ref: https://imgur.com/a/s5JJBa2

That being said, the '++' needs to be revised for smaller resolutions by being enlarged sufficiently to be used as a menu icon
